    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for this house i'm buying in toronto. i'm kinda confused. whats escrow actually and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in the context of buying a house in Toronto, is essentially a secure holding place for funds and documents until all the conditions of the sale are met. Think of it like a temporary, neutral holding area, managed by a third party—usually a lawyer or a real estate professional. It's crucial because it protects both you, the buyer, and the seller, ensuring that the money only changes hands once the property transfer is officially complete. Without it, you'd be handing over your hard-earned cash before you've actually secured the deed to the house, which is a riskier proposition.",
      "source": "target",
