    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so like, who actually holds onto the money while it's sitting there? is it just a bank or someone else?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The entity holding the money, the escrow agent, isn't always just a regular bank, though some banks certainly offer these services. More often, in a transaction like this in Toronto, it's your real estate lawyer who acts as the escrow agent. They are the designated, trusted third party, holding the funds in a specific trust account until the closing date. This is vital because they are legally bound to only release the funds to the seller once all the paperwork is signed and the title transfer is confirmed.",
      "source": "target",
